,"text":"","conceptType":"place","pos":{"x":-974.5915178571436,"y":209.55208333333402},"id":"sc-1a52cbd6-7c29-423d-93b3-0e67b241a71c","imageCsiteID":"csite-f0ecce98-1aaf-41f7-877b-48d7ecefed0d"},"sc-2d236223-a924-4b88-9cc8-bf743d89a492":{"type":"textscrap","entityID":"sc-1a52cbd6-7c29-423d-93b3-0e67b241a71c","text":"...The ManMart Manifesto and the battle of the Manateers","conceptType":"note","pos":{"x":-1014.0969446655738,"y":327.72900547607816},"id":"sc-2d236223-a924-4b88-9cc8-bf743d89a492"},"sc-58092642-b4e5-4190-8c9a-5085af42dc97":{"type":"entity","text":"Manlonius Monks","conceptType":"faction","pos":{"x":-489.3831845238099,"y":372.85937500000017},"id":"sc-58092642-b4e5-4190-8c9a-5085af42dc97"},"sc-4713df14-59c5-4acb-bd7f-97249c7ddc3d":{"type":"textscrap","entityID":"sc-58092642-b4e5-4190-8c9a-5085af42dc97","text":"...Sophisticated upper echelon of Manlantian culture's old world before the ManbillionMillionTrillionTomitons arrived","conceptType":"note","pos":{"x":-494.0691986151075,"y":447.4326297900549},"id":"sc-4713df14-59c5-4acb-bd7f-97249c7ddc3d","size":{"w":185,"h":143}},"sc-18b4ee33-506a-47f3-bf39-3171fd4b34a0":{"parents":["sc-58092642-b4e5-4190-8c9a-5085af42dc97","sc-4713df14-59c5-4acb-bd7f-97249c7ddc3d"],"type":"textscrap","conceptType":"note","text":"Manlonius Monks are an ancient sect skilled in manipulating time streams through mindful reflection. Their temple is camouflaged as a funhouse hall of mirrors, guarding the secrets of the cosmos.","pos":{"x":-281.77211968798764,"y":440.4497565746051},"entityID":"sc-58092642-b4e5-4190-8c9a-5085af42dc97","id":"sc-18b4ee33-506a-47f3-bf39-3171fd4b34a0","loading":false,"textgenItemID":"textgen-2d18f9a3-9aa7-4ebb-8e87-f275db678e13"},"sc-871a016f-bde9-4f96-8424-f12b77e7867e":{"parents":["sc-2d236223-a924-4b88-9cc8-bf743d89a492"],"type":"textscrap","conceptType":"note","text":"The ManMart Manifesto inspired a splinter group, the Manateers, who sought to overthrow the ManTomitons using weaponized hall-of-mirrors technologies. This sparked a multiversal conflict as the Mirrorborne intervened, fracturing realities across the Cosmic Man-naissance.","pos":{"x":-805.2794343284438,"y":488.3181264761379},"id":"sc-871a016f-bde9-4f96-8424-f12b77e7867e","loading":false,"textgenItemID":"textgen-30fd7ce2-7b22-4efe-80cb-a06d5755c553"},"sc-148f58ce-0a55-4ebb-a37a-d0267f020aff":{"parents":["sc-0c2a21b1-ac20-4bea-bbb0-ab12253d02f6"],"type":"textscrap","conceptType":"note","text":"The Mantomitons' sacred relics are actually fragments of a shattered cosmic mirror, allowing their supreme leader to peer into alternate realities. Through ritualistic reflections, the Mantomiton elders divine knowledge from infinite possibilities.","pos":{"x":-1338.1848136791484,"y":731.662663702804},"entityID":"sc-0c2a21b1-ac20-4bea-bbb0-ab12253d02f6","id":"sc-148f58ce-0a55-4ebb-a37a-d0267f020aff","loading":false,"textgenItemID":"textgen-9b438bc8-e5b2-48e4-9cae-20223ed96216"}}